subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis.
Male: fore femur moderately incrassate (variations existed, ratio length/width about 3.60–4.75), indentation on ventral surface with small tooth on proximal edge, and a stout sub-apical tooth (in more slender fore femur, indentation usually smaller, 
Figs. 47, 48
). Male genitalia large: segment 8, pygophore and proctiger elongate; paramere prominent, falciform with pointed apex (
Fig. 33
), endosoma as in 
Chen & Nieser (1993
: 
Fig. 62
). Female: tergum 7 sub-triangular, sometimes apex medially produced (
Figs. 49, 50
); sternum 7 large, posterior part constricted and produced two separate lobes, sometimes curved dorsad, completely enclosing genitalia, the notch between two lobes narrow, angular (
Fig. 51
).
